me Thorpe (August 29, 1926 – September 25, 2018) was an American television-and-film director and producer. Actor and director Richard Thorpe was his father.Thorpe served as the executive producer of 33 episodes of The Untouchables (starring Robert Stack) during the series' 2nd season (1960–61). Thorpe also served as executive producer of Harry O, the 1973-75 David Janssen TV series. \nThorpe won an Emmy award for his work on an episode of Kung Fu. In 2003, a Golden Palm Star on the Palm Springs, California, Walk of Stars was dedicated to him and his father.Thorpe died in Santa Barbara, California, at the age of 92 from natural causes. He was buried at Desert Memorial Park in Cathedral City, California.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T15:30:38.278523+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 2378, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerry_Thorpe"}], "uuid": "5ff93610-8d8d-4ace-a187-1cb55941b295", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "21818", "external_references": [{"id": 10189, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q3177509"}, {"id": 10190, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "87499984"}, {"id": 10191, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n85376636"}, {"id": 10192, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n85376636"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T21:23:05.251213+10:00"}, {"id": 81391, "name": "Kathryn Grayson", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2250602, "title": "Rio Rita", "work_id": 95598, "role": "cast", "role_id": 33, "is_primary": false}], "also_known_as": "Zelma Kathryn Elisabeth Hedrick", "date_of_birth": "1922-02-09", "date_of_death": "2010-02-17", "genders": [{"id": 5, "name": "Female", "slug": "female"}], "languages": [{"id": 1, "name": "English", "slug": "english"}], "places_of_operation": [{"id": 1, "name": "United States of America", "slug": "united-states-of-america"}], "biography": "Kathryn Grayson (born Zelma Kathryn Elisabeth Hedrick; February 9, 1922 – February 17, 2010) was an American actress and coloratura soprano.From the age of twelve, Grayson trained as an opera singer. She was under contract to Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer by the early 1940s, soon establishing a career principally through her work in musicals. After several supporting roles, she was a lead performer in such films as Thousands Cheer (1943), Anchors Aweigh (1945) with Frank Sinatra and Gene Kelly, and Show Boat (1951) and Kiss Me Kate (1953), both with Howard Keel.When film musical production declined, she worked in theatre, appearing in Camelot (1962–1964). Later in the decade she performed in several operas, including La bohème, Madama Butterfly, Orpheus in the Underworld and La traviata.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T15:47:11.404150+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 4470, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kathryn_Grayson"}], "uuid": "63f43770-f766-494e-88e8-c1ff1ee9d9ef", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "33717", "external_references": [{"id": 25226, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q234117"}, {"id": 29738, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "112818298"}, {"id": 29739, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n85376512"}, {"id": 29740, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n85376512"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T22:02:27.893357+10:00"}, {"id": 81390, "name": "Ben Rogers", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2224290, "title": "Fabric of a Dream: the Fletcher Jones Story", "work_id": 95594, "role": "cast", "role_id": 33, "is_primary": false}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T16:24:1